   result.message = (\n                f\"Rate limit warning: {minute_count} writes in last minute \"\n                f\"(limit: {self._config.writes_per_minute})\"\n            )\n            logger.warning(\n                \"rate_limit_minute_exceeded\",\n                current=minute_count,\n                limit=self._config.writes_per_minute,\n            )\n\n        if session_exceeded:\n            msg = (\n                f\"Rate limit warning: {session_count} writes this session \"\n                f\"(limit: {self._config.writes_per_session})\"\n            )\n            if result.message:\n                result.message += f\"; {msg}\"\n            else:\n                result.message = msg\n            logger.warning(\n                \"rate_limit_session_exceeded\",\n                current=session_count,\n                limit=self._config.writes_per_session,\n            )\n\n        return result\n\n    def reset(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Reset all counters and timestamps (useful for testing).\"\"\"\n        with self._lock:\n            self._timestamps.clear()\n            self._session_count = 0\n            self._stats = RateLimiterStats()\n```\n\n### 2. Batch Context Integration in Store.save()\n\nIn `/src/tapps_brain/store.py`, the `save()` method signature (lines 243-258) includes:\n\n```python\ndef save(\n    self,\n    key: str,\n    value: str,\n    tier: str = \"pattern\",\n    source: str = \"agent\",\n    source_agent: str = \"unknown\",\n    scope: str = \"project\",\n    tags: list[str] | None = None,\n    branch: str | None = None,\n    confidence: float = -1.0,\n    agent_scope: str = \"private\",\n    *,\n    skip_consolidation: bool = False,\n    batch_context: str | None = None,\n) -> MemoryEntry | dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Save or update a memory entry.\n\n    Returns the saved ``MemoryEntry``, or an error dict if RAG safety\n    blocks the content.\n\n    Args:\n        key: Unique identifier for the memory.\n        value: Memory content.\n        tier: Memory tier (architectural, pattern, context).\n        source: Source of the memory (human, agent, inferred, system).\n        source_agent: Identifier of the agent saving the memory.\n        scope: Visibility scope (project, branch, session).\n        agent_scope: Hive propagation scope (private, domain, hive).\n        tags: Tags for categorization.\n        branch: Git branch name (required when scope=branch).\n        confidence: Confidence score (-1.0 for auto from source).\n        skip_consolidation: If True, skip auto-consolidation check.\n        batch_context: Operation context for rate limit exemption\n            (e.g. \"import_markdown\", \"seed\", \"federation_sync\", \"consolidate\").\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Rate limit check at line 298:**\n```python\n# Rate limit check (H6a) — warn-only, never blocks\nrate_result = self._rate_limiter.check(batch_context=batch_context)\nif rate_result.minute_exceeded or rate_result.session_exceeded:\n    logger.warning(\n        \"memory_save_rate_warning\",\n        key=key,\n        minute_count=rate_result.current_minute_count,\n        session_count=rate_result.current_session_count,\n    )\n```\n\n### 3. Batch Context Exempt Operations\n\nThe four batch contexts exempt from rate limiting are defined in `BATCH_EXEMPT_CONTEXTS`:\n\n- **`import_markdown`** - Used when importing MEMORY.md files via `markdown_import.py`\n- **`seed`** - Used when seeding memory store from project profiles in `seeding.py`\n- **`federation_sync`** - Used for cross-project memory federation operations (defined in constants but operation functions need to pass this context)\n- **`consolidate`** - Used when consolidating similar memory entries in `auto_consolidation.py`\n\n### 4. Current Usage in Seeding (seeding.py)\n\nIn `/src/tapps_brain/seeding.py`, the `_do_seed()` function (starting line 94) performs bulk saves during initial profile-based seeding. Currently, these calls **do NOT pass `batch_context=\"seed\"`**. Examples:\n\n```python\n# Lines 104-113\nstore.save(\n    key=\"project-type\",\n    value=f\"Project type is {profile.project_type}\",\n    tier=MemoryTier.architectural.value,\n    source=MemorySource.system.value,\n    source_agent=_SOURCE_AGENT,\n    scope=MemoryScope.project.value,\n    tags=_make_seed_tags(\"project-type\"),\n    confidence=confidence,\n)\n```\n\nAll seeding `store.save()` calls in `seeding.py` omit the `batch_context` parameter.\n\n### 5. Consolidation Persistence (auto_consolidation.py)\n\nIn `/src/tapps_brain/auto_consolidation.py`, the `_persist_consolidated_entry()` function (lines 176-215) saves consolidated entries. Currently **does NOT pass `batch_context=\"consolidate\"`**:\n\n```python\n# Lines 186-195\nstore.save(\n    key=consolidated.key,\n    value=consolidated.value,\n    tier=_get_enum_value(consolidated.tier),\n    source=_get_enum_value(consolidated.source),\n    source_agent=consolidated.source_agent,\n    scope=_get_enum_value(consolidated.scope),\n    tags=consolidated.tags,\n    confidence=consolidated.confidence,\n)\n```\n\n### 6. Markdown Import (markdown_import.py)\n\nIn `/src/tapps_brain/markdown_import.py`, the `_parse_and_import()` function (lines 91-118) and `_import_daily_note()` (lines 154-190) both call `store.save()` but **do NOT pass `batch_context=\"import_markdown\"`**:\n\n```python\n# Lines 109-114\nstore.save(\n    key=key,\n    value=value,\n    tier=tier.value,\n    source=MemorySource.system.value,\n)\n\n# Lines 183-188\nstore.save(\n    key=key,\n    value=value,\n    tier=MemoryTier.context.value,\n    source=MemorySource.system.value,\n)\n```\n\n### 7. Test Coverage\n\nComprehensive test coverage exists in `/tests/unit/test_rate_limiter.py`:\n\n- **`TestRateLimiterConfig`** - Tests default and custom configurations\n- **`TestRateLimitResult`** - Tests result data structure defaults\n- **`TestSlidingWindowRateLimiter`** - Tests core functionality:\n  - `test_under_limit_allowed()` - Writes under limit pass\n  - `test_over_minute_limit_warns()` - Exceeding minute limit logs warnings but allows writes\n  - `test_over_session_limit_warns()` - Exceeding session limit logs warnings\n  - `test_both_limits_exceeded()` - Combined message handling\n  - `test_disabled_limiter()` - Disabled config returns defaults\n  - `test_sliding_window_expiry()` - Old timestamps pruned after 60 seconds\n  - **`test_batch_context_exempt()`** - **All four exempt contexts bypass rate limiting** (lines 134-147)\n  - **`test_batch_context_non_exempt()`** - Non-exempt batch_context still rate limited (lines 149-157)\n  - `test_stats_tracking()` - Anomaly counter accumulation\n  - **`test_stats_exempt_tracking()`** - **Exempt writes counted separately** (lines 174-182)\n  - `test_reset()` - State clearing\n  - `test_config_property()` - Configuration property access\n- **`TestBatchExemptContexts`** - Validates all four context strings exist in frozenset\n\nKey test assertions (line 144):\n```python\nfor ctx in BATCH_EXEMPT_CONTEXTS:\n    result = limiter.check(batch_context=ctx)\n    assert result.allowed is True\n    assert result.minute_exceeded is False\n    assert result.session_exceeded is False\n```\n\n### Summary: Implementation Status\n\nThe rate limiter is **fully implemented and tested**, with:\n\n1. **Mechanism**: Sliding window with 1-minute rolling window + session counter\n2. **Mode**: Warn-only (never blocks writes)\n3. **Defaults**: 20 writes/minute, 100 writes/session\n4. **Exemptions**: Four batch context operations are exempt from rate limit counting\n5. **Tracking**: Separate stats for exempt vs. regular writes\n\n**However**, the actual **integration in batch operations is incomplete**:\n- `seeding.py` saves do not pass `batch_context=\"seed\"`\n- `markdown_import.py` saves do not pass `batch_context=\"import_markdown\"`\n- `auto_consolidation.py` saves do not pass `batch_context=\"consolidate\"`\n- `federation_sync` context is defined but no federation sync implementation found that uses it\n\nThe batch_context parameter exists in the API and is tested in isolation, but the calling code hasn't been updated to leverage the exemption mechanism yet."}],"totalDurationMs":76646,"totalTokens":78834,"totalToolUseCount":35,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":910,"cache_read_input_tokens":74322,"output_tokens":3602,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":910},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
